                                                  written lines: 22 29; Watermarks on , and on . The first watermark is a hand, the second watermark is a vase with a crescent at the top and a monogramm (CO?), similar to 3603 (dated to 1646, England).Single leaves were written by another scribe; their codicological elements being different from those by the original scribe. At the bottom of these pages, one can discern the scribe's attempts to enlarge the letters in order to fit the text into the remaining empty spaces. These leaves were glued into the margins of now-missing pages which were torn out from the original Pentateuch.
